<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>AI Roast My Website - Get Brutally Honest Feedback</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar">
    <div class="nav-brand">Roast My Website</div>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <% if (user) { %>
        <a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
        <a href="/auth/logout">Logout</a>
      <% } else { %>
        <a href="/auth/login">Login</a>
        <a href="/auth/register">Sign Up</a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1 class="hero-title">Get Your Website <span class="neon-text">Brutally Roasted</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Paste your URL and our AI will deliver a hilariously honest critique of your design, copy, and UX. No feelings spared.</p>

      <% if (error) { %>
        <div class="error-message"><%= error %></div>
      <% } %>

      <form class="roast-form" id="roast-form">
        <div class="input-group">
          <input type="text" id="url-input" name="url" placeholder="https://your-website.com" required class="url-input">
          <button type="submit" class="roast-btn">Roast It</button>
        </div>
      </form>

      <div id="loading" class="loading hidden">
        <div class="spinner"></div>
        <p>Analyzing your website with zero mercy...</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div id="result-container" class="hidden"></div>

  <section class="features">
    <h2>What You Get</h2>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">&#x1F3A8;</div>
        <h3>Design Disaster Score</h3>
        <p>We rate your visual choices on a scale of "minimalist genius" to "absolute chaos."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">&#x270D;</div>
        <h3>Copy Catastrophe Score</h3>
        <p>Your words will be judged. Harshly. Is your copy compelling or cringe?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">&#x1F5B1;</div>
        <h3>UX Nightmare Score</h3>
        <p>Can users actually navigate your site, or is it a digital escape room?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="social-proof">
    <h2>Wall of Shame</h2>
    <div class="testimonials">
      <div class="testimonial-card">
        <p class="quote">"I showed this to my designer and they quit. 10/10 would roast again."</p>
        <p class="author">- A former startup founder</p>
      </div>
      <div class="testimonial-card">
        <p class="quote">"The AI was more honest than any feedback I have ever gotten from my team."</p>
        <p class="author">- Someone who needed to hear the truth</p>
      </div>
      <div class="testimonial-card">
        <p class="quote">"My website got a 2/10. I have never been more motivated to redesign."</p>
        <p class="author">- A humbled developer</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <p>AI Roast My Website - No feelings were considered in the making of these roasts.</p>
  </footer>

  <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
